  "theory": {
    "intro": "**Simplifying** a fraction means writing it as an equivalent fraction with the smallest possible whole numbers. Divide the numerator and denominator by a common factor until none remains.",
    "facts": [
      "A fraction is **fully simplified** when the numerator and denominator share no common factor except $1$.",
      "Dividing top and bottom by the **HCF** simplifies in one step: $\\frac{8}{12} = \\frac{8 \\div 4}{12 \\div 4} = \\frac{2}{3}$.",
      "You can also divide by common factors repeatedly until the fraction cannot be reduced any further."
    ],
    "steps": [
      "Find the HCF of the numerator and denominator.",
      "Divide both by the HCF.",
      "Check the result has no remaining common factor."
    ]
  },
